🛡️ Navigation & System Info (Pt. 1 & 2)
Command & Description
whoami___Shows the current logged-in user.
pwd___Print Working Directory (shows exactly where you are).
ls___-laList all files, including hidden (-a) with details (-l).
cd___[dir]Change Directory. (cd .. goes up one level).
file [file] Identifies the actual file type (header analysis).cat 
[file] Reads the contents of a file to the screen.
history Shows a list of all previously executed commands.
touch [name]Creates a new empty file.
mkdir [name]Creates a new directory.
cp [src] [dst]Copies a file. Use -r for folders.
mv [src] [dst]Moves or renames a file/folder.
rm [file]Deletes a file. Use -rf for folders (Warning: permanent!).
grep "text" [file]Searches for specific text inside a file.
find / -name [name]Searches the entire system for a specific file by name.
🔐 Permissions & Access (Pt. 2)
ssh [user]@[ip] Securely logs into a remote machine.
su [user]Switch User (requires that user's password).
sudo [cmd]Runs a command with root/admin privileges.
chmod [777] [file]Changes file permissions (Read/Write/Execute).
chown [user] [file]Changes the owner of a file.
⚙️ System Management (Pt. 3)
nano [file] Simple terminal-based text editor.
apt install [pkg] Installs new software (requires sudo).
ps aux Lists every running process on the system.
top Real-time Task Manager (CPU/RAM usage).
kill [PID] Forces a process to stop using its ID number.
systemctl [action] [svc] Starts/Stops/Restarts background services (e.g., apache2).
crontab -e Edits the automation schedule for timed tasks.
🌐 Networking (Pt. 3)
ip addrShows your local IP address and network interfaces.
ping [ip/web]Tests connection to another machine.
